value.0: A protector of Winya Ravana, these elves were called from Evermeet itself.

This shield is commonly mass produced during times of war to protect valuable field officers. Sometimes they gather in merchants inventories during periods of peace or when a surplus has been made. They are definitely more practical than elaborate, a fairly straight-forward protection.
A protector of the winya council and its administration.

All seemed lost the dark day that the island Zanshibon was absorbed into the abyss. Many lamented the great evil that had happened. One however who had once called the island home and had been selling his wares when it was lost found new focus and drive as a craftsman. They say he forged many shields and sets of armor so the agents of the abyss could be made to pay. His last shield made days before his death, his last defence is potent piece of protection indeed.

This scabbard can be used to display a scabbard on your character's back. Using again will empty the scabbard. Using a third time will remove the item from your back.

((Job System Item))

Simple and smooth, this timepiece ticks along. Consisting only of a numbered metal loop and a series of crossing beams, one's mind boggles at how it might operate.

There is something familiar in this curious timepiece. You have seen it before. Or maybe it comes from a time yet to arrive. In the twinkling of a eye, one might see it in the reflecting metal. A huge figure in purple and gold armor, hourglasses and clocks embedded therein. And behind it, looming, a many-legged creature of shadow, not of this world or any other.

Perhaps time will tell. Perhaps time has already told.

In the Year of the Shield, the area once known as Stonehold was conquered by the Emberblaze family alongside the Dark Flight, a fell cabal of chromatic dragons. This newly renamed settlement of Wyrmhold would fight a fierce battle with Benwick, ultimately destroying it before being destroyed itself.

It is not known when these idols were made, nor whose remains they now hold. The spirit of that time, however, when dragons waged war over the Amian Isle, continues to rage on through its power. It will bestow the gift of purging fire to any weapon that would claim it.

It is not known when these idols were made, nor whose remains they now hold. The spirit of that time, however, when dragons waged war over the Amian Isle, continues to rage on through its power. It will bestow the gift of purging fire to any weapon that would claim it.

All seemed lost the dark day that the island Zanshibon was absorbed into the abyss. Many lamented the great evil that had happened. One however who had once called the island home and had been selling his wares when it was lost found new focus and drive as a craftsman. They say he forged many shields and sets of armor so the agents of the abyss could be made to pay. His last shield made days before his death, his last defence is potent piece of protection indeed.

Simple and smooth, this timepiece ticks along. Consisting only of a numbered metal loop and a series of crossing beams, one's mind boggles at how it might operate.

There is something familiar in this curious timepiece. You have seen it before. Or maybe it comes from a time yet to arrive. In the twinkling of a eye, one might see it in the reflecting metal. A huge figure in purple and gold armor, hourglasses and clocks embedded therein. And behind it, looming, a many-legged creature of shadow, not of this world or any other.

Perhaps time will tell. Perhaps time has already told.

A dizzying array of written works, each catalogued according to some fashion you cannot fathom. A number of them appear to be written in foreign tongues altogether.

We the children of Kazeen hear and obey.  The darkness of the Rat shall decend upon the unworthy.  You reading this are one of the wise, one of the chosen.  You have looked past your brethern and see the pettyness of thier ambition. Come now and see the workings of Kazeen.

The text goes on to describe the tales of a god known as "Kazzen" apparently a lesser daemon of death and diesease.  Of particular note is a passage on the fall of Zbiel.

"The third week the faithful were rewarded.  With fires about the city the coup from beneath the earth was almost complete. The victory was sealed when Bomir called forth the avatar of Kazeen. Who shall walk this earth for 1000 years yet."
The Cult of The Horned Rat Vol 1

Pours a clear reddish amber with a frothy, foamy head that settles into a thin sudsy lacing. It has aromas of lightly toasted grains, a apple and grape fruitiness with a little orange zest, earthy yeast, and a soft floral hoppiness. 

Pleasant tasting, toasted grassy grains and caramelized sugary maltiness, earthy, peppery yeastiness, a light fruitiness, a bit apple and orange, spicy hops with a soft, but lingering bitterness, a slight taste of alcohol towards the end, the alcohol provides a subtle warming in the palate, and a dry grainy, subtle fruity, spicy finish.

Ice wine is a type of dessert wine produced from grapes that have been frozen while still on the vine. This results in a smaller amount of more concentrated, very sweet wine. Due to the labour-intense and risky production process resulting in relatively small amounts of wine, ice wines are generally quite expensive.
